column2: .) Sampling error: Figures marked with "s" are subject to standard errors of more than ±20% at 95% statistical confidence. .) Restricition for combining different features : As the road freight transport statistics is based on a sample survey, for some features the sampling error would be too large to combine it with other features. Only the most important features can be combined and displayed unrestricted. .) Data availability: Main results of road freight transport statistics are available free of charge. More detailed results (e.g. border crossing points) can be obtained with a subscription. For special data requests alternative evaluations can be offered. .) Data provenience: Road freight transport statistics has provided information about the transports of Austrian companies using heavy goods vehicles and articulated lorries registered in Austria on national and international roads and is performed as sampling survey. .) Legal basis: Bundesstatistikgesetz 2000 idgF (Anlage II); Straßen- und Schienengüterverkehrsstatistikgesetz, BGBl. Nr. 142/1983; Straßen- und Schienengüterverkehrsstatistik-Verordnung, BGBl. II Nr. 393/1995, idF BGBl. II Nr. 119/2005; .) Updating: Updating of time series: quarterly, all data for periods of less than a year are provisional until a complete reference year is released. After having finished and released a complete reference year all provisional data will be replaced with definitive data. Last updating: [2020-11-30] .)
